    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, an engine renowned for its individual throttle bodies and 8,000 RPM redline. This example is equipped with the desirable 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a factory-spec variable M differential lock for superior power delivery. Significant preventative maintenance has been addressed, including professional VANOS servicing and rear subframe reinforcement to ensure structural rigidity. The suspension utilizes a track-tested MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup, providing the precise feedback and sharp turn-in characteristic of the chassis. While the exterior shows light road use, the mechanical vitals are robust, making this a compelling choice for the driver who prioritizes analog performance and engineering purity.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Used vehicle in good condition. Minor exterior wear. Well-maintained engine and clean interior. All maintenance records available. Runs well.",
      "price": 29500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_11_listing_4",
      "firm_id": "sybil_11",
      "description": "This meticulously maintained vehicle offers a perfect balance of performance and reliability. The exterior retains a deep, glossy finish with only minor road wear consistent with careful use. Inside, the premium leather upholstery remains supple and free of tears, while all electronic features, from the dual-zone climate control to the premium sound system, function exactly as intended. Mechanically, the car is sound, having followed a strict preventative maintenance schedule with all service records documented and available for review. It sits on a set of high-performance tires with significant tread life remaining and recently underwent a full fluid service. This is a turn-key example for a discerning buyer who values a car that has been respected and professionally cared for throughout its life.",
      "price": 34800.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_5_listing_5",
      "firm_id": "sybil_5",
      "description": "Presenting a distinguished example of automotive engineering, this vehicle has been curated for the professional who demands both performance and reliability. Meticulously maintained and showing consistent care, it offers a refined driving experience and a commanding road presence. Each component has been vetted to ensure it meets our dealership's rigorous standards for quality, providing the next owner with a sophisticated balance of utility and prestige.",
      "price": 36450.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_6_listing_6",
      "firm_id": "sybil_6",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m parting ways with my trusty ride, and she\u2019s been an absolute joy to drive. It\u2019s in really solid shape\u2014well-loved, dependable, and still looks fantastic on the road! It runs like a dream and is totally ready for its next adventure. Come take it for a spin; I'm sure you'll fall in love with it just like I did!",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.8,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-strung S54B32 power plant. This 3.2L inline-six utilizes individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system that has been recently calibrated for peak volumetric efficiency. The chassis is structurally sound, featuring documented subframe reinforcement to mitigate common floor pan fatigue. Power is channeled through a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transmission and a variable M differential lock, ensuring optimal torque distribution during corner exit. The suspension remains tight, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and a multi-link rear setup with refreshed bushings to maintain factory-spec kinematics. While the exterior shows honest patina consistent with its age, the drivetrain and cooling system are in excellent health, making this a purist\u2019s driver that is ready for the canyon or the track.",
